The user can either enter a month in its full name, abbreviation
in 3 letters, or in number. E.g: January as January, Jan., Jan, and 1

The user must enter a year in a non-negative number and all the digits.
E.g: Valid inputs for 1999 is only 1999, not 99...

A year is either a common year of 365 days or leap year of 366 days.
Every year that is divisible by 4 is a leap year, except for years
that divisible by 100, but not by 400. 